    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's an interesting way to put it. When you talk about that \"raw reality\" and \"gritty vibe,\" are you saying that to be authentic, the clothes should actually reflect certain socioeconomic backgrounds or specific ethnic lifestyles? Like, if I'm designing for an urban audience, should I be leaning into specific tropes or imagery associated with certain neighborhoods or groups to make it feel \"real\"?",
